To the guy who asked
>Will an artist take AI References
The answer I have is "Yes, but don't expect them to."
It also probably depends on exactly what you're asking them to do with the reference. "Keep her looking like this" is more likely to be accepted it than "copy this picture exactly".
I also suspect asking them to draw something like Mila Mink would be more likely to be rejected compared to an AI-Generated OC you never shared with anyone, as they'll likely ask you to keep quiet about the AI reference.
Giving them a lot of normal/non-AI references before the AI would probably help as well, since it shows you're serious with the request and not just an "AI bro" in their eyes.
Emailing/DMing them on a burner and just asking is another option, but IMO it's way easier to tell someone to fuck off when they ask one thing compared to giving you a bunch of stuff to read over and then saying "btw do you have anything against using this AI pic as a looks reference?" at the end, since the latter shows you're a serious client compared to the former.
